1
00:01:37,797 --> 00:01:38,198
Du Yan.

2
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,200
You're eighteen today.

3
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:42,202
We're talking now

4
00:01:42,202 --> 00:01:42,869
as two adults.

5
00:01:46,639 --> 00:01:47,707
Your condition

6
00:01:49,008 --> 00:01:50,343
is indeed quite serious.

7
00:01:50,844 --> 00:01:52,278
So we need you to work with us

8
00:01:53,046 --> 00:01:54,514
and face it positively together.

9
00:01:55,248 --> 00:01:56,316
If possible,

10
00:01:56,683 --> 00:01:58,184
replacing it with a healthy heart

11
00:01:58,751 --> 00:02:00,153
would be the safer option.

12
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:02,121
But waiting for a donor

13
00:02:02,589 --> 00:02:03,590
does come with

14
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:04,491
many uncertainties.

15
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:06,693
So it's basically luck.

16
00:02:08,728 --> 00:02:09,996
But before that,

17
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:11,965
we can implant

18
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:12,765
an artificial heart first.

19
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,368
It's just a small pump

20
00:02:15,869 --> 00:02:17,036
placed inside your chest

21
00:02:17,904 --> 00:02:19,205
to help your heart work.

22
00:02:19,772 --> 00:02:20,974
Then you won't be

23
00:02:21,007 --> 00:02:21,841
as weak as you are now.

24
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,013
We've already discussed all this

25
00:02:27,013 --> 00:02:27,947
with your parents.

26
00:02:32,285 --> 00:02:32,752
Dr. Fang,

27
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:35,889
have you ever felt

28
00:02:37,223 --> 00:02:38,358
that sometimes

29
00:02:39,592 --> 00:02:40,360
your work

30
00:02:40,393 --> 00:02:41,394
goes against nature?

31
00:02:42,562 --> 00:02:43,630
Since my heart

32
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,398
was born this way,

33
00:02:46,032 --> 00:02:46,833
the system was set

34
00:02:46,866 --> 00:02:48,668
to last only a little over ten years.

35
00:02:48,935 --> 00:02:50,570
Why insist on repairing it,

36
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:51,371
replacing it,

37
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:52,505
or installing a machine

38
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:53,373
to do its job?

39
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,009
Why are you always trying to defy fate?

40
00:02:56,876 --> 00:02:57,510
Survival of the fittest.

41
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:58,878
Why not let nature take its course?

42
00:03:00,213 --> 00:03:02,549
Letting nature take its course doesn't mean giving up.

43
00:03:03,883 --> 00:03:05,552
It means facing the outcome calmly

44
00:03:05,585 --> 00:03:06,786
after doing everything possible, right?

45
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,955
After all, survival is a human instinct.

46
00:03:08,988 --> 00:03:10,523
For most people.

47
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:12,792
Not me.

48
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:16,296
For some people,

49
00:03:18,231 --> 00:03:19,766
death may even be a gift.

50
00:03:24,804 --> 00:03:25,405
Dr. Fang,

51
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,174
you don't need to give me a birthday present.

52
00:03:31,477 --> 00:03:32,512
But could you help me fulfill

53
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,746
one birthday wish?

54
00:03:35,848 --> 00:03:36,316
Go ahead.

55
00:03:37,684 --> 00:03:38,918
In your ICU,

56
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,522
can a patient refuse

57
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:43,590
family visits?

58
00:03:45,525 --> 00:03:46,993
I already made my wish.

59
00:03:48,127 --> 00:03:49,729
I never want to see them again.

60
00:03:51,831 --> 00:03:52,432
I don't.

61
00:03:59,305 --> 00:04:00,807
Given your condition,

62
00:04:02,976 --> 00:04:04,110
it wouldn't be appropriate for us

63
00:04:04,143 --> 00:04:05,078
to forcibly stop them.

64
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:07,714
But I can relay your request.

65
00:04:08,648 --> 00:04:09,048
See?

66
00:04:10,717 --> 00:04:12,118
Not every birthday wish

67
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:13,119
can come true.

68
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:17,223
Forget it.

69
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,127
Please also wish your friend

70
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,961
a happy birthday.

71
00:04:40,046 --> 00:04:40,647
I'm done.

72
00:04:40,913 --> 00:04:41,714
Should I wait for you for dinner?

73
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:16,049
Come on.

74
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:17,317
You need to pay attention.

75
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,384
Director Lin has played a bomb.

76
00:05:21,087 --> 00:05:22,388
Triple with a pair. Two cards left.

77
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:24,123
Xiao Lin,

78
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:26,092
you played right into my hand.

79
00:05:28,361 --> 00:05:29,395
Five cards.

80
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:30,963
Pass.

81
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:32,165
Of course you can't beat that.

82
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:32,865
Can't beat it. Can't beat it.

83
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:33,666
Sorry.

84
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:36,035
Three, four, five, six, seven. I'm out.

85
00:05:36,235 --> 00:05:37,036
Director Zhang,

86
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:38,638
you played right into my hand.

87
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:42,041
When did Xiao Lin

88
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:43,076
learn to go easy on people?

89
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:44,210
Look, you played a single.

90
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:44,844
Then a pair.

91
00:05:44,944 --> 00:05:46,212
Every card helped me.

92
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:47,280
Really.

93
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:47,914
Come on, Director Sheng.

94
00:05:47,914 --> 00:05:49,048
Don't be upset. Come on, Director Lin.

95
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:50,650
No need. I'll drink Director Sheng's glass.

96
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:53,252
Director Lin.

97
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:55,254
Director Lin is in high spirits today.

98
00:05:55,321 --> 00:05:55,755
Come on.

99
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:56,189
Let's drink together.

100
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,156
Come on, all together.

101
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:57,990
Thank you.

102
00:05:57,990 --> 00:05:58,958
Director Lin can really hold his liquor.

103
00:05:59,225 --> 00:05:59,992
Thank you, Xiao Lin.

104
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:07,800
Is he back?

105
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:09,969
No.

106
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:12,705
Maybe he's still in surgery.

107
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:18,911
This day last year,

108
00:06:20,246 --> 00:06:22,115
we took Xiaorui to the zoo

109
00:06:22,148 --> 00:06:23,049
to celebrate together.

110
00:06:25,485 --> 00:06:26,486
The year before that,

111
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:28,454
we went camping

112
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:29,822
for his birthday.

113
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:33,626
I even made

114
00:06:33,626 --> 00:06:34,794
a birthday cake for him.

115
00:06:36,162 --> 00:06:36,629
Director Lin.

116
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,232
Everyone, look over here.

117
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:42,235
The day after tomorrow is Qianqian's birthday.

118
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:43,669
Today, let's all

119
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,405
wish her a happy birthday, okay?

120
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:47,640
Okay.

121
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:50,943
Happy birthday to you.

122
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:53,146
Happy birthday...

123
00:06:53,346 --> 00:06:54,247
Don't worry, Xiaorui.

124
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:55,314
I promise

125
00:06:56,315 --> 00:06:57,183
your twentieth birthday

126
00:06:58,651 --> 00:07:00,153
will be easier

127
00:07:01,187 --> 00:07:01,721
and happier than mine.

128
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:10,430
Happy birthday to you.

129
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:14,367
Happy birthday to you.

130
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:17,370
Is Qianqian eighteen now?

131
00:07:19,238 --> 00:07:20,106
You look younger and younger.

132
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,174
And prettier too.

133
00:07:24,477 --> 00:07:26,913
I originally planned to have dinner

134
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,714
after work today.

135
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,394
Good thing you came out with me.

136
00:07:42,094 --> 00:07:43,429
At least I've recharged a little.

137
00:07:44,931 --> 00:07:46,232
Otherwise, I really didn't want

138
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,367
to stay in that house alone.

139
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:52,572
After we finish,

140
00:07:52,572 --> 00:07:53,773
you should head home early too.

141
00:07:54,073 --> 00:07:54,874
You've worked hard.

142
00:07:55,174 --> 00:07:55,641
It's fine.

143
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,610
You can recharge me too.

144
00:07:59,679 --> 00:08:00,446
You've worked hard,

145
00:08:00,713 --> 00:08:02,648
our little Cardiology whirlwind.

146
00:08:05,952 --> 00:08:06,953
This one worked hardest.

147
00:08:07,954 --> 00:08:09,155
I think it's great.

148
00:08:09,455 --> 00:08:10,389
The contrast is really fun.

149
00:08:10,923 --> 00:08:12,391
Your female fans have something new to look forward to.

150
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:13,559
This is now

151
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:14,827
my go-to mealtime entertainment.

152
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:16,429
Even Mom has seen it.

153
00:08:17,363 --> 00:08:18,531
When we're less busy,

154
00:08:18,798 --> 00:08:19,932
Mom and I will

155
00:08:19,966 --> 00:08:21,067
record a reaction video for you.

156
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:26,472
I'm the Cardiology whirlwind.

157
00:08:27,039 --> 00:08:29,175
Let me hear your heart.

158
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,202
Er-Yi, turn on the light.

159
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:34,573
Business at the shop

160
00:09:34,607 --> 00:09:35,841
has always been good.

161
00:09:36,709 --> 00:09:37,443
Don't worry.

162
00:09:38,477 --> 00:09:39,712
I've been taking care of everything for you.

163
00:09:42,214 --> 00:09:42,882
But some

164
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,483
regular customers have asked me

165
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:46,118
why there haven't been

166
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:47,253
any new products lately.

167
00:09:48,521 --> 00:09:49,121
I don't know

168
00:09:49,155 --> 00:09:50,089
how to answer them.

169
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:53,626
I also thought about

170
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,329
posting a store-closure notice.

171
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,167
But I couldn't bring myself

172
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:02,134
to shut it down.

173
00:10:04,203 --> 00:10:05,104
Xiaorui,

174
00:10:06,706 --> 00:10:08,040
today is your birthday.

175
00:10:09,642 --> 00:10:10,943
You're another year older.

176
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:12,645
By the way,

177
00:10:13,212 --> 00:10:14,647
I ate your favorite cake

178
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:17,216
for you today.

179
00:10:18,884 --> 00:10:20,319
And your flowers and plants—

180
00:10:21,587 --> 00:10:22,989
I've taken great care of them.

181
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:29,762
You can see them too, right?

182
00:10:35,935 --> 00:10:36,969
I'm fine, Director.

183
00:10:37,069 --> 00:10:37,670
Slowly. Careful.

184
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:38,804
I don't need help. I...

185
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:39,605
Director Sheng, I'm home.

186
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:39,972
Xiao Fang.

187
00:10:41,073 --> 00:10:41,674
Director Sheng.

188
00:10:41,707 --> 00:10:42,675
I drank a little, but I'm fine.

189
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:43,876
Here.

190
00:10:43,876 --> 00:10:44,510
Give it to me.

191
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:46,345
Get some rest.

192
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:48,347
Thank you, Director Sheng.

193
00:10:48,547 --> 00:10:49,015
I'll be going, then.

194
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:52,885
How much did you drink?

195
00:10:52,885 --> 00:10:53,319
I'm fine.

196
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:54,687
Not much.

197
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:06,265
Drink some hot water.

198
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:17,910
Where did you go?

199
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:21,080
I don't even know.

200
00:11:21,313 --> 00:11:22,748
Director Sheng took me

201
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:23,849
somewhere to sing,

202
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:25,117
then we played cards.

203
00:11:26,786 --> 00:11:28,054
My luck was terrible today.

204
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,588
I kept getting bad hands,

205
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:31,123
so I kept losing,

206
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,191
and kept drinking.

207
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:34,093
More and more.

208
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:36,796
And you couldn't

209
00:11:36,796 --> 00:11:37,863
send me a message?

210
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,667
Did you? Where's my phone?

211
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:44,370
Were you looking for me?

212
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,008
What day is today?

213
00:11:53,612 --> 00:11:54,213
What day?

214
00:11:55,147 --> 00:11:55,648
I remember.

215
00:11:56,482 --> 00:11:57,216
I remember.

216
00:11:58,284 --> 00:11:59,952
Tomorrow... tomorrow I have to

217
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:00,953
go on a business trip.

218
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:18,871
He doesn't need another birthday.

219
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,275
He'll always be twenty.

220
00:14:01,207 --> 00:14:01,807
Dr. Fang.

221
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:03,876
What is it?

222
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,111
Can you help me with something?

223
00:14:26,232 --> 00:14:27,967
You know Du Yan's condition.

224
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,268
He urgently needs surgery.

225
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:30,569
But now there's

226
00:14:30,569 --> 00:14:31,470
an even more serious problem.

227
00:14:37,142 --> 00:14:38,444
Du Yan wrote this.

228
00:14:39,078 --> 00:14:40,713
He... he wrote this?

229
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:41,814
He wrote it himself.

230
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:44,216
Why?

231
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:45,918
We're confused too.

232
00:14:46,185 --> 00:14:47,152
So we wanted to ask you

233
00:14:47,253 --> 00:14:48,587
why he's so resistant.

234
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:49,989
This...

235
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,323
Where are you going?

236
00:14:51,423 --> 00:14:51,924
I'm going to see him.

237
00:14:52,157 --> 00:14:53,759
No. You can't go like this.

238
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:54,193
I'm his father.

239
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:54,894
Why can't I?

240
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,362
Yesterday, Du Yan clearly said

241
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:57,763
he didn't want you to visit.

242
00:14:58,063 --> 00:14:59,031
If you go in

243
00:14:59,031 --> 00:14:59,531
with this attitude,

244
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:00,466
you'll only upset him more.

245
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:01,767
Ignore him.

246
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:02,735
We're his parents.

247
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:03,402
We decide for him.

248
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:04,637
He can't refuse surgery.

249
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:05,638
If he needs treatment, he gets treatment.

250
00:15:05,804 --> 00:15:06,906
He just turned eighteen.

251
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:08,040
He's an adult now.

252
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,108
He has the right to make

253
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:10,142
his own medical decisions.

254
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,010
But, doctor,

255
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:11,844
even if he's eighteen,

256
00:15:11,944 --> 00:15:13,212
we're still his parents.

257
00:15:13,312 --> 00:15:14,446
We only want what's best for him.

258
00:15:14,513 --> 00:15:15,614
He has to listen to us.

259
00:15:15,714 --> 00:15:17,516
And even if we force him into surgery,

260
00:15:17,683 --> 00:15:18,784
perioperative monitoring

261
00:15:18,884 --> 00:15:19,752
and treatment afterward

262
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:21,587
still require his cooperation.

263
00:15:24,957 --> 00:15:25,891
Then what are we supposed to do?

264
00:15:26,525 --> 00:15:27,393
All we can do now

265
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:28,727
is keep trying to talk to him,

266
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:29,995
help him stop resisting treatment,

267
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:30,863
and keep him from giving up.

268
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,431
But as his parents,

269
00:15:32,731 --> 00:15:33,265
do you truly not know

270
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:34,333
why he's like this?

271
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:41,040
Maybe before...

272
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:41,573
I...

273
00:15:43,442 --> 00:15:43,876
No.

274
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,110
There was no reason.

275
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:45,911
No.

276
00:15:46,011 --> 00:15:46,946
He's just rebellious.

277
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:47,947
He always wants to oppose us.

278
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:51,350
Mr. Du,

279
00:15:52,751 --> 00:15:53,519
we're doctors.

280
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:55,154
We'll do everything we can

281
00:15:55,154 --> 00:15:56,555
to treat his physical condition.

282
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:58,957
But his psychological issues

283
00:15:59,525 --> 00:16:00,893
require your cooperation.

284
00:16:06,665 --> 00:16:07,866
I'm truly sorry, doctor.

285
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:09,134
I'll try to persuade him again.

286
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,970
Please think of a way

287
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:12,638
to help us. Thank you.

288
00:16:14,273 --> 00:16:15,007
Old Du.

289
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:25,551
Let's start preparing.

290
00:16:26,251 --> 00:16:27,286
Keep communicating with Du Yan

291
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:27,920
about his willingness for surgery.

292
00:16:28,253 --> 00:16:29,088
At the same time, prepare

293
00:16:29,088 --> 00:16:30,122
the artificial heart device

294
00:16:30,122 --> 00:16:30,956
and the surgical plan.

295
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:32,291
Dr. Liu,

296
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:34,827
anything to add?

297
00:16:35,694 --> 00:16:36,228
I...

298
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:38,931
Director Zhou explained everything clearly.

299
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:40,599
I have nothing to add.

300
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:41,633
I'll follow Director Zhou's plan.

301
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,369
Then which director

302
00:16:43,369 --> 00:16:44,403
from your department will operate?

303
00:16:46,438 --> 00:16:46,972
Well...

304
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:48,707
That...

305
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:51,710
I still need to go back and ask.

306
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:57,916
I'll return to the ICU first.

307
00:17:13,432 --> 00:17:13,832
See?

308
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:15,567
It's different when a good friend visits.

309
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:16,869
He looks much better.

310
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:18,203
He's even smiling.

311
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:20,773
Then may I borrow

312
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:21,707
your phone?

313
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,243
I just want to make one call.

314
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:39,691
All of this

315
00:17:40,159 --> 00:17:40,993
is happening without

316
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:42,795
my participation.

317
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:45,831
They decide my fate

318
00:17:46,465 --> 00:17:48,267
without asking my opinion.

319
00:17:49,601 --> 00:17:50,102
Sometimes,

320
00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:51,904
I really want to interrupt everyone

321
00:17:52,638 --> 00:17:53,238
and say this:

322
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:57,276
in the end, who exactly is on trial?

323
00:17:57,309 --> 00:17:57,810
Teacher Jiang.

324
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:00,712
Do you have a moment?

325
00:18:00,879 --> 00:18:01,647
I'd like to talk.

326
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:08,587
Teacher Jiang,

327
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:10,255
Mr. Peng's

328
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,690
lung infection hasn't improved these past two days.

329
00:18:12,324 --> 00:18:13,692
So for the short term,

330
00:18:13,725 --> 00:18:14,827
he probably can't come off

331
00:18:14,893 --> 00:18:16,028
the ventilator.

332
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:17,763
But if this continues,

333
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:18,597
long-term oral intubation

334
00:18:18,630 --> 00:18:19,932
can cause many complications.

335
00:18:20,466 --> 00:18:21,233
So we're preparing

336
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:22,568
to perform a tracheostomy.

337
00:18:23,001 --> 00:18:24,269
We'll use this opening

338
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,270
to support his breathing.

339
00:18:25,504 --> 00:18:26,105
That way,

340
00:18:26,205 --> 00:18:27,606
it's safer for long-term use.

341
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:34,012
No.

342
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:35,514
Teacher Jiang,

343
00:18:35,647 --> 00:18:36,648
a tracheostomy

344
00:18:36,715 --> 00:18:37,916
can reduce damage

345
00:18:37,916 --> 00:18:39,318
to the vocal cords and trachea.

346
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:41,286
It also makes suctioning and clearing secretions more effective.

347
00:18:41,753 --> 00:18:43,255
And look at Mr. Peng now.

348
00:18:43,322 --> 00:18:44,623
That large tube in his throat

349
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:45,757
is uncomfortable too.

350
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:49,495
During the procedure,

351
00:18:49,528 --> 00:18:50,329
we'll use anesthesia.

352
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:50,963
It won't hurt.

353
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,275
His baseline condition is already poor,

354
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,244
and his lung infection is severe.

355
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:07,312
Without a tracheostomy,

356
00:19:08,046 --> 00:19:08,914
it may affect

357
00:19:08,947 --> 00:19:09,882
his subsequent treatment.

358
00:19:11,116 --> 00:19:12,050
I hope you'll think it over carefully.

359
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:20,192
If I ever reach that point,

360
00:19:22,394 --> 00:19:24,129
I don't want invasive resuscitation.

361
00:19:27,232 --> 00:19:28,400
Everyone dies eventually.

362
00:19:29,434 --> 00:19:30,068
I hope

363
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:31,703
to die with some dignity.

364
00:19:52,090 --> 00:19:53,358
Why?

365
00:19:54,293 --> 00:19:55,427
Why are you being unreasonable again?

366
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,129
Teacher Jiang and Mr. Peng

367
00:19:57,129 --> 00:19:57,829
have such a good relationship.

368
00:19:58,163 --> 00:19:58,931
Why won't she agree

369
00:19:58,964 --> 00:19:59,932
to a tracheostomy?

370
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,834
A tracheostomy is invasive treatment.

371
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,636
Mr. Peng is nearly eighty.

372
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:05,871
I can understand that.

373
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:09,841
But Du Yan is only eighteen,

374
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:12,411
and he refuses all treatment too.

375
00:20:13,512 --> 00:20:14,813
What is going on?

376
00:20:14,846 --> 00:20:16,248
Why can't they see reason?

377
00:20:17,282 --> 00:20:18,784
Every patient is different.

378
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:20,552
Sometimes what traps people

379
00:20:20,652 --> 00:20:21,753
isn't just the illness itself.

380
00:20:23,255 --> 00:20:24,356
As doctors,

381
00:20:24,823 --> 00:20:25,691
we can only do

382
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:26,491
everything in our power,

383
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:27,326
put ourselves in their shoes,

384
00:20:27,326 --> 00:20:28,227
and think for them.

385
00:20:29,094 --> 00:20:29,995
Only then are we truly

386
00:20:30,028 --> 00:20:30,729
helping them solve their problems.

387
00:20:32,798 --> 00:20:33,265
What did you say?

388
00:20:35,033 --> 00:20:36,034
You can actually say something like that?

389
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:37,569
What's wrong with it?

390
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:39,371
Whoever you are,

391
00:20:39,605 --> 00:20:40,906
get out of Ye Sisi's body.

392
00:20:43,008 --> 00:20:43,976
Crazy.

393
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,751
The girl has changed.

394
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:54,953
This is the information

395
00:20:55,053 --> 00:20:55,988
on the artificial heart you wanted.

396
00:20:57,189 --> 00:20:58,156
How is that patient?

397
00:20:58,390 --> 00:21:00,092
I heard he just turned eighteen.

398
00:21:00,492 --> 00:21:00,826
Yes.

399
00:21:01,293 --> 00:21:02,127
He just had his birthday.

400
00:21:02,995 --> 00:21:04,196
But the difficult part now

401
00:21:04,396 --> 00:21:05,430
is that he doesn't want treatment.

402
00:21:06,198 --> 00:21:07,399
He refuses every intervention.

403
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:09,434
Why?

404
00:21:11,470 --> 00:21:12,604
It probably has something to do with his parents.

405
00:21:13,705 --> 00:21:14,239
But they won't tell us

406
00:21:14,239 --> 00:21:15,073
anything.

407
00:21:16,241 --> 00:21:17,042
Is there anything

408
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:18,310
I can do to help?

409
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:24,583
Zhang Zhen told me

410
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,385
he interviewed

411
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:27,653
at the insurance company you recommended.

412
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:29,054
He said it went well.

413
00:21:29,554 --> 00:21:29,955
Yes.

414
00:21:30,355 --> 00:21:31,723
The position

415
00:21:31,723 --> 00:21:33,925
is in medical claims review.

416
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:35,594
So it's related to his training.

417
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:36,795
And the pay is pretty good.

418
00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:37,763
Thank you

419
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:39,665
for treating it seriously.

420
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:41,233
I wouldn't mind

421
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:42,334
if Director Zhou bought me another meal.

422
00:21:43,335 --> 00:21:43,802
No problem.

423
00:21:44,703 --> 00:21:45,404
Let's begin.

424
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:50,842
Why are you sighing?

425
00:21:51,209 --> 00:21:52,010
Our last

426
00:21:52,444 --> 00:21:53,278
Organ-Protecting Health Exercise

427
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:54,746
got excellent numbers.

428
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,048
We should build on that momentum.

429
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:00,452
What are we filming this time?

430
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:02,587
Cardiology Whirlwind's

431
00:22:02,788 --> 00:22:03,955
Heart-Protecting Fitness Fist.

432
00:22:05,357 --> 00:22:06,158
What?

433
00:22:06,558 --> 00:22:07,426
Let's record the opening first.

434
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:09,795
Three, two, one.

435
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:11,363
Hello, everyone.

436
00:22:11,596 --> 00:22:13,398
I'm the Cardiology Whirlwind.

437
00:22:13,598 --> 00:22:15,033
Let me hear your heart.

438
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:16,668
Today I'm bringing you

439
00:22:16,768 --> 00:22:18,003
the Heart-Protecting Fitness Fist.

440
00:22:18,603 --> 00:22:19,271
Good.

441
00:22:19,805 --> 00:22:20,238
That works.

442
00:22:22,574 --> 00:22:23,041
Dr. Fang,

443
00:22:23,709 --> 00:22:24,443
I didn't expect you

444
00:22:24,443 --> 00:22:25,043
to call me.

445
00:22:25,677 --> 00:22:26,812
Strictly speaking,

446
00:22:28,413 --> 00:22:29,514
we weren't classmates.

447
00:22:31,149 --> 00:22:31,917
We were more like

448
00:22:33,085 --> 00:22:33,552
roommates,

449
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:35,320
or

450
00:22:36,521 --> 00:22:36,922
fellow inmates.

451
00:22:40,292 --> 00:22:41,226
We didn't know each other before.

452
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:43,595
Three years ago,

453
00:22:43,628 --> 00:22:44,429
our parents sent us

454
00:22:45,430 --> 00:22:46,932
to a so-called correctional academy.

455
00:22:50,068 --> 00:22:50,802
I hated

456
00:22:50,802 --> 00:22:51,503
my name from childhood.

457
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:52,637
Jin Miao.

458
00:22:53,405 --> 00:22:54,406
People always called me "Golden Retriever."

459
00:22:55,107 --> 00:22:55,707
Du Yan told me

460
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:56,842
people also gave him nicknames.

461
00:22:57,209 --> 00:22:58,009
They called him "Belly Button."

462
00:22:58,443 --> 00:22:59,745
But when our names were put together,

463
00:22:59,911 --> 00:23:01,113
they happened to cover metal, wood, water, fire, and earth.

464
00:23:02,314 --> 00:23:03,648
So the two of us,

465
00:23:03,949 --> 00:23:04,649
partners in misery, became close.

466
00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:05,751
We became good friends.

467
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:08,487
We helped each other

468
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:10,322
and encouraged each other.

469
00:23:11,990 --> 00:23:12,824
That's how we survived

470
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:13,692
those darkest days.

471
00:23:14,593 --> 00:23:15,127
Darkest?

472
00:23:15,961 --> 00:23:18,029
What kind of correctional academy was it?

473
00:23:18,997 --> 00:23:20,198
What did they "correct"?

474
00:23:20,766 --> 00:23:21,800
Everything.

475
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,335
Anything our parents

476
00:23:23,368 --> 00:23:24,236
thought was wrong.

477
00:23:26,004 --> 00:23:27,072
Take me, for example.

478
00:23:27,472 --> 00:23:28,406
I liked video games

479
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:30,108
and making game commentary videos.

480
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:32,310
My parents thought I was wasting my life

481
00:23:32,644 --> 00:23:33,445
and needed to be fixed.

482
00:23:34,112 --> 00:23:35,080
They lied and said we were going on a trip,

483
00:23:35,747 --> 00:23:36,681
then sent me there.

484
00:23:39,284 --> 00:23:40,051
What about Du Yan?

485
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,687
His reason was ridiculous.

486
00:23:43,722 --> 00:23:44,289
At that time,

487
00:23:44,322 --> 00:23:45,423
his grades kept falling.

488
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:46,892
His parents were very dissatisfied.

489
00:23:47,993 --> 00:23:48,360
They said

490
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:49,528
they'd raised him spoonful by spoonful,

491
00:23:49,795 --> 00:23:50,629
and he didn't know how to appreciate it.

492
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:52,330
They also said that whenever

493
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:53,265
he was alone in his room,

494
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:54,332
he always shut the door.

495
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:56,067
Who knew what

496
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:56,568
he was doing in there?

497
00:23:57,636 --> 00:23:58,637
His parents would always barge in

498
00:23:58,637 --> 00:23:59,304
without knocking.

499
00:24:00,172 --> 00:24:01,873
Once, Du Yan locked the door.

500
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,074
His father kicked it

501
00:24:03,108 --> 00:24:04,176
and smashed a huge hole in it.

502
00:24:05,243 --> 00:24:06,444
After that, he was sent there.

503
00:24:07,879 --> 00:24:09,114
All because he locked

504
00:24:09,147 --> 00:24:10,215
his own bedroom door.

505
00:24:11,249 --> 00:24:11,850
That's how absurd it was.

506
00:24:13,118 --> 00:24:15,387
His father looks quiet,

507
00:24:16,354 --> 00:24:17,122
but at home,

508
00:24:17,155 --> 00:24:18,023
he has a violent temper.

509
00:24:20,025 --> 00:24:22,127
So how did they "correct" you?

510
00:24:23,762 --> 00:24:25,197
So-called military-style training.

511
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:27,199
We got up before dawn every day,

512
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:29,868
ran and exercised,

513
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:30,969
cleaned the dorm,

514
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:32,103
and recited rules.

515
00:24:33,171 --> 00:24:34,439
If anything was even slightly wrong,

516
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:37,309
we were put in solitary confinement,

517
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,110
locked up,

518
00:24:41,012 --> 00:24:41,513
and worse.

519
00:24:47,853 --> 00:24:48,520
Du Yan

520
00:24:48,553 --> 00:24:49,754
has those old scars too.

521
00:24:53,391 --> 00:24:54,326
Punching and kicking,

522
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:56,194
burns—

523
00:24:56,828 --> 00:24:57,929
those were considered mild.

524
00:25:01,466 --> 00:25:02,267
The most terrifying thing

525
00:25:04,369 --> 00:25:05,036
was electric shocks.

526
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:07,639
Electric shocks?

527
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:25,290
Jin Miao,

528
00:25:27,893 --> 00:25:28,693
are you okay?

529
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:29,628
I'm fine.

530
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:34,599
The pain of electric shocks

531
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:35,734
was worse than death.

532
00:25:37,969 --> 00:25:38,803
I could endure a lot,

533
00:25:40,238 --> 00:25:41,273
but in the end, even I broke.

534
00:25:42,307 --> 00:25:43,441
Du Yan was much more obedient than me,

535
00:25:44,209 --> 00:25:45,076
but he was punished many times too.

536
00:25:46,144 --> 00:25:46,912
Why?

537
00:25:47,445 --> 00:25:49,047
He always felt weak back then.

538
00:25:49,748 --> 00:25:50,682
He'd get breathless just climbing stairs.

539
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:53,752
He couldn't complete

540
00:25:54,052 --> 00:25:54,686
the daily exercise and labor.

541
00:25:55,253 --> 00:25:56,354
The instructors thought he was lazy.

542
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:58,189
So he suffered

543
00:25:58,223 --> 00:25:59,391
more corporal punishment than we did.

544
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:02,093
His heart function was probably

545
00:26:02,127 --> 00:26:03,361
already poor at that time.

546
00:26:05,196 --> 00:26:05,797
Let go of me!

547
00:26:06,431 --> 00:26:06,965
Stay still!

548
00:26:07,032 --> 00:26:07,599
Let go!

549
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:10,268
He didn't do it on purpose!

550
00:26:10,535 --> 00:26:11,369
Let go! Let go!

551
00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:12,437
He didn't...

552
00:26:14,105 --> 00:26:15,006
Let him go!

553
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:19,010
Let go!

554
00:26:34,693 --> 00:26:35,026
Charge it.

555
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:37,796
Don't pull me! Don't touch me!

556
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:38,630
Don't touch me!

557
00:26:38,797 --> 00:26:39,831
Please, don't touch me!

558
00:26:40,532 --> 00:26:41,366
Please don't touch me!

559
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:43,168
Don't touch me!

560
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:49,074
Did your parents

561
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:50,475
know what happened to you?

562
00:26:51,343 --> 00:26:52,043
They always thought

563
00:26:52,077 --> 00:26:52,911
the academy was just

564
00:26:52,944 --> 00:26:54,245
a strict boarding school.

565
00:26:56,481 --> 00:26:57,849
Du Yan escaped once.

566
00:27:00,352 --> 00:27:01,119
But his parents

567
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:02,153
forcibly took him back.

568
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:05,190
They only cared about the result.

569
00:27:07,826 --> 00:27:08,293
Mom.

570
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:10,528
I'm begging you.

571
00:27:10,562 --> 00:27:12,063
Take me home.

572
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:14,799
I promise I'll listen from now on.

573
00:27:14,833 --> 00:27:16,167
I'll never make you angry again.

574
00:27:16,201 --> 00:27:18,103
I'll die if I stay here.

575
00:27:18,203 --> 00:27:19,237
Please.

576
00:27:19,237 --> 00:27:19,671
Please take me away.

577
00:27:19,671 --> 00:27:20,271
Du Yan,

578
00:27:21,039 --> 00:27:22,574
you're just too used to comfort.

579
00:27:23,441 --> 00:27:24,409
At home, everything is handed to you.

580
00:27:24,409 --> 00:27:25,076
You never lift a finger.

581
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:26,144
You've never suffered at all.

582
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:28,313
You don't appreciate anything or feel grateful.

583
00:27:28,613 --> 00:27:29,648
You need to stay here

584
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:30,081
and toughen yourself up.

585
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:30,715
No, Dad.

586
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:32,751
This place isn't

587
00:27:32,751 --> 00:27:33,518
what you think it is.

588
00:27:33,551 --> 00:27:35,153
It isn't a correctional academy.

589
00:27:35,186 --> 00:27:36,588
They torture us every day.

590
00:27:36,654 --> 00:27:37,756
They force us to do hard labor.

591
00:27:37,756 --> 00:27:38,556
Whenever we make a mistake,

592
00:27:38,556 --> 00:27:39,090
they tie us up...

593
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:39,424
Du Yan.

594
00:27:40,558 --> 00:27:41,626
You've disappointed me so much.

595
00:27:42,193 --> 00:27:42,627
Mom.

596
00:27:43,762 --> 00:27:44,696
Not one word is true.

597
00:27:44,696 --> 00:27:45,530
You've become a habitual liar.

598
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:46,431
I'm not lying, Dad.

599
00:27:46,765 --> 00:27:47,332
If I'd known you'd turn out like this,

600
00:27:47,365 --> 00:27:48,199
I never should've had you.

601
00:27:49,567 --> 00:27:50,602
Study hard and change yourself.

602
00:27:51,036 --> 00:27:51,569
I'm telling you,

603
00:27:51,603 --> 00:27:52,437
this is not negotiable.

604
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:54,105
If you don't change, never come home.

605
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:54,973
Let's go.

606
00:27:55,573 --> 00:27:55,874
Mom.

607
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:56,474
Go. Go.

608
00:27:57,108 --> 00:27:57,509
Mom.

609
00:27:58,076 --> 00:27:58,510
Mom.

610
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:00,278
Mom! Mom!

611
00:28:01,112 --> 00:28:01,513
Son.

612
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,147
Let go of me!

613
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:03,948
Let go!

614
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:06,084
What right do you have to treat me like this?

615
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:07,285
I'm not a prisoner!

616
00:28:07,452 --> 00:28:09,087
See? Look at the son you raised.

617
00:28:09,454 --> 00:28:09,788
Let's go.

618
00:28:10,989 --> 00:28:11,523
Son.

619
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:14,526
People like you

620
00:28:14,559 --> 00:28:16,528
don't deserve to be parents!

621
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:24,469
You'll regret this!

622
00:28:28,473 --> 00:28:29,207
How did you eventually get out?

623
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,108
How did you eventually get out?

624
00:28:31,009 --> 00:28:31,876
The academy was shut down.

625
00:28:33,645 --> 00:28:34,479
Otherwise, we don't know

626
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:35,480
how long we would've been locked up.

627
00:28:36,948 --> 00:28:37,882
The academy only let parents

628
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:38,850
see obedient,

629
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:40,285
compliant children.

630
00:28:41,686 --> 00:28:42,520
Later, when the news broke,

631
00:28:42,587 --> 00:28:43,955
some parents finally woke up.

632
00:28:44,956 --> 00:28:46,024
But regret came too late.

633
00:28:47,192 --> 00:28:48,026
Other parents,

634
00:28:50,628 --> 00:28:51,863
like Du Yan's,

635
00:28:53,531 --> 00:28:54,799
would rather deceive themselves

636
00:28:54,999 --> 00:28:55,967
than admit

637
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,268
they personally sent their child

638
00:28:57,335 --> 00:28:58,470
into a living hell.

639
00:29:02,674 --> 00:29:03,074
Dr. Fang,

640
00:29:04,275 --> 00:29:05,243
I've actually been

641
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:08,279
worried about him these past two days.

642
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:11,349
That day at the hospital,

643
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:13,751
Dahuo told me,

644
00:29:14,085 --> 00:29:14,586
"Sanshui."

645
00:29:16,488 --> 00:29:16,888
"What is it?"

646
00:29:21,793 --> 00:29:22,727
"This time,

647
00:29:24,395 --> 00:29:25,396
I may not get better."

648
00:29:30,802 --> 00:29:31,436
"Don't talk nonsense."

649
00:29:32,670 --> 00:29:33,204
"Really."

650
00:29:33,838 --> 00:29:34,639
"I'm not."

651
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:38,176
"But you know what?"

652
00:29:39,677 --> 00:29:40,612
"These past few days,

653
00:29:40,645 --> 00:29:41,746
I've actually felt

654
00:29:43,948 --> 00:29:45,750
quite relaxed."

655
00:29:47,152 --> 00:29:48,386
"I don't have to see my dad every day,

656
00:29:49,154 --> 00:29:51,089
or keep forcing myself

657
00:29:51,789 --> 00:29:52,557
to act like a good son,

658
00:29:54,959 --> 00:29:55,960
an obedient son."

659
00:29:58,997 --> 00:30:00,198
"I feel free."

660
00:30:04,402 --> 00:30:05,670
"Maybe this is fine too."

661
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:07,572
I know that for

662
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:10,875
Dahuo,

663
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:13,211
he'd rather be sick in the hospital

664
00:30:13,244 --> 00:30:14,312
than return to

665
00:30:15,246 --> 00:30:15,914
that suffocating home.

666
00:30:18,149 --> 00:30:18,883
But honestly,

667
00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:28,026
I'm scared.

668
00:30:28,026 --> 00:30:29,127
Du Yan has already

669
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:30,562
fainted twice this year.

670
00:30:32,363 --> 00:30:32,964
You truly didn't know?

671
00:30:34,232 --> 00:30:34,833
No.

672
00:30:34,866 --> 00:30:35,834
What about when he was

673
00:30:37,735 --> 00:30:38,570
at that academy?

674
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:39,871
Back then,

675
00:30:40,171 --> 00:30:40,638
he already had chest tightness,

676
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:42,273
fatigue,

677
00:30:42,874 --> 00:30:44,976
and reduced exercise tolerance.

678
00:30:45,210 --> 00:30:45,944
He was punished by the instructors for it,

679
00:30:46,945 --> 00:30:48,012
and even beaten.

680
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:51,916
You didn't know any of that?

681
00:30:52,317 --> 00:30:53,084
Everything he suffered

682
00:30:53,151 --> 00:30:54,252
may very well

683
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,989
have worsened his condition.

684
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:01,793
It was his father who insisted he go.

685
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,494
Every time I saw him covered in injuries,

686
00:31:03,595 --> 00:31:04,629
as his mother,

687
00:31:04,629 --> 00:31:06,197
how could I not feel heartbroken?

688
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:10,168
How could I not suffer?

689
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:13,838
We only wanted what was best for him.

690
00:31:14,405 --> 00:31:16,708
We spent so much money.

691
00:31:16,908 --> 00:31:18,443
The tuition was extremely expensive.

692
00:31:19,444 --> 00:31:20,879
We had no choice.

693
00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:23,548
After he came out,

694
00:31:25,283 --> 00:31:27,185
he did seem more obedient.

695
00:31:27,352 --> 00:31:29,254
But this time, I don't understand

696
00:31:30,088 --> 00:31:31,122
why he's being so stubborn.

697
00:31:31,923 --> 00:31:33,291
Because this time,

698
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:34,158
he finally doesn't have to live

699
00:31:35,426 --> 00:31:36,894
under your control.

700
00:31:36,894 --> 00:31:37,729
He can finally

701
00:31:49,507 --> 00:31:49,841
Du Yan.

702
00:31:50,308 --> 00:31:50,675
Du Yan.

703
00:31:51,175 --> 00:31:51,609
Du Yan!

704
00:31:54,712 --> 00:31:55,613
Now that we

705
00:31:55,613 --> 00:31:56,414
know the reason,

706
00:31:56,614 --> 00:31:57,548
we'll find a way together.

707
00:31:58,516 --> 00:31:59,150
But you have to work with us.

708
00:31:59,150 --> 00:31:59,717
Dr. Xiaoran.

709
00:32:01,786 --> 00:32:02,320
What's wrong?

710
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:05,823
What happened?

711
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:06,624
Is it Yanyan?

712
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:07,091
Wait.

713
00:32:11,796 --> 00:32:12,597
What's his condition now?

714
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:16,968
Okay, I'm coming right away.

715
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:31,983
Doctor! Doctor!

716
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:33,384
Is it our Yanyan?

717
00:32:33,484 --> 00:32:33,985
Family members,

718
00:32:34,152 --> 00:32:35,320
don't panic. We'll do our best.

719
00:32:36,087 --> 00:32:37,789
She does look pitiful.

720
00:32:38,089 --> 00:32:39,123
She clearly loves her child,

721
00:32:39,724 --> 00:32:40,892
yet still let it come to this.

722
00:32:43,828 --> 00:32:45,229
She spent half her life as a teacher.

723
00:32:45,763 --> 00:32:46,931
What kinds of children and parents

724
00:32:46,931 --> 00:32:47,632
hasn't she seen?

725
00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:49,934
Some people spend their whole lives

726
00:32:49,934 --> 00:32:51,169
never obtaining power,

727
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,371
until they become parents.

728
00:32:57,041 --> 00:32:58,710
He has recurrent ventricular fibrillation and unstable circulation.

729
00:32:59,077 --> 00:32:59,944
Vasoactive drugs

730
00:33:00,011 --> 00:33:00,678
aren't working either.

731
00:33:01,079 --> 00:33:02,080
His cardiac contractility is very poor.

732
00:33:02,347 --> 00:33:02,914
We need to start

733
00:33:02,947 --> 00:33:03,348
ECMO immediately.

734
00:33:03,514 --> 00:33:04,449
Otherwise, he may not survive.

735
00:33:05,249 --> 00:33:05,883
In his condition,

736
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:06,250
ECMO

737
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:07,118
can only be a bridge.

738
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:08,286
Ultimately, he'll still need

739
00:33:08,286 --> 00:33:08,987
an artificial heart.

740
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:10,188
If we put him on ECMO,

741
00:33:10,254 --> 00:33:11,022
has the family signed consent?

742
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:11,923
I'm going now.

743
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:12,957
I'll prepare.

744
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:19,564
Du Yan is in critical condition.

745
00:33:19,731 --> 00:33:20,965
Medication and resuscitation

746
00:33:20,965 --> 00:33:21,532
have both failed.

747
00:33:21,966 --> 00:33:23,134
The only option is to start

748
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:23,568
ECMO immediately

749
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:24,802
to buy time

750
00:33:24,802 --> 00:33:25,470
for an artificial heart implant.

751
00:33:25,903 --> 00:33:26,437
But ECMO itself

752
00:33:26,471 --> 00:33:27,705
also carries risks.

753
00:33:28,039 --> 00:33:29,173
We need your informed consent.

754
00:33:29,407 --> 00:33:30,008
Take a look.

755
00:33:31,743 --> 00:33:33,911
I'll call his father.

756
00:33:45,089 --> 00:33:46,691
Pick up!

757
00:33:49,761 --> 00:33:51,229
If you don't sign now, it'll be too late.

758
00:33:51,963 --> 00:33:55,166
I'll sign. No, we have to wait for his father.

759
00:33:57,635 --> 00:33:58,703
He's not answering.

760
00:34:00,171 --> 00:34:01,639
What matters more—your son's life

761
00:34:01,672 --> 00:34:03,007
or your husband's orders?

762
00:34:03,775 --> 00:34:05,476
What should I do, doctor?

763
00:34:05,910 --> 00:34:07,011
This is when your son

764
00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:08,112
needs you most.

765
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:09,013
You have to stay strong.

766
00:34:10,314 --> 00:34:11,582
You need to trust the doctors.

767
00:34:11,849 --> 00:34:12,750
They feel

768
00:34:12,750 --> 00:34:13,718
the same way you do.

769
00:34:13,918 --> 00:34:15,520
They only want to save your son.

770
00:34:16,954 --> 00:34:18,289
Don't panic. Calm down.

771
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:19,690
Read it.

772
00:34:19,791 --> 00:34:20,958
If there are no questions, sign quickly.

773
00:34:33,037 --> 00:34:33,371
Doctor.

774
00:34:33,371 --> 00:34:33,905
Please wait.

775
00:34:34,038 --> 00:34:34,639
Doctor.

776
00:34:34,839 --> 00:34:36,874
Save my child, doctor.

777
00:34:37,608 --> 00:34:40,077
He's my only child.

778
00:34:44,015 --> 00:34:44,949
Doctor.

779
00:34:45,483 --> 00:34:48,519
What am I going to do? My child...

780
00:34:50,988 --> 00:34:52,423
It's okay. Trust the doctors.

781
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:53,291
He'll be all right.

782
00:34:53,691 --> 00:34:54,325
Everything will be okay.

783
00:35:15,913 --> 00:35:16,314
Ouyang.

784
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,182
I heard Dongli has

785
00:35:18,182 --> 00:35:18,583
a boy

786
00:35:18,583 --> 00:35:20,551
with left ventricular noncompaction

787
00:35:20,852 --> 00:35:22,153
being considered for an artificial heart.

788
00:35:22,687 --> 00:35:22,987
Yes.

789
00:35:23,154 --> 00:35:24,055
Cardiology admitted him.

790
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:25,623
I've already given

791
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:26,357
the artificial heart information to Director Zhou.

792
00:35:26,724 --> 00:35:27,925
But I heard the patient himself

793
00:35:28,025 --> 00:35:29,727
is resistant to treatment.

794
00:35:29,994 --> 00:35:30,761
So the specifics

795
00:35:30,795 --> 00:35:31,829
of the surgery haven't been decided.

796
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:33,965
That's a major order.

797
00:35:34,232 --> 00:35:35,333
Stay on top of it.

798
00:35:37,201 --> 00:35:38,169
If they do it,

799
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:39,237
it'll be Dongli's

800
00:35:39,437 --> 00:35:40,705
first artificial heart implantation, right?

801
00:35:42,173 --> 00:35:42,874
Most likely,

802
00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:46,144
Sheng Nian will operate himself.

803
00:35:47,445 --> 00:35:48,846
It could also be Lin Yi.

804
00:35:49,146 --> 00:35:50,014
After all, the patient

805
00:35:50,014 --> 00:35:50,748
is under Director Zhou.

806
00:35:51,516 --> 00:35:52,650
I heard the two of them

807
00:35:52,683 --> 00:35:53,284
are still at odds.

808
00:35:54,685 --> 00:35:55,186
Hard to say.

809
00:36:06,264 --> 00:36:07,231
Du Yan's father came back,

810
00:36:07,365 --> 00:36:08,332
but he may as well not have.

811
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:10,034
One moment he blamed Du Yan's mother

812
00:36:10,067 --> 00:36:11,335
for acting on her own without waiting for him.

813
00:36:11,702 --> 00:36:12,436
The next, he asked

814
00:36:12,436 --> 00:36:13,404
whether, while Du Yan

815
00:36:13,404 --> 00:36:14,105
was unconscious,

816
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,673
they could also sign

817
00:36:15,706 --> 00:36:16,440
the consent for the artificial heart surgery.

818
00:36:27,919 --> 00:36:28,920
Du Yan now has

819
00:36:28,953 --> 00:36:29,921
ECMO support,

820
00:36:30,321 --> 00:36:31,289
but at this rate,

821
00:36:31,289 --> 00:36:31,989
once he's stable,

822
00:36:32,390 --> 00:36:33,958
will he need the artificial heart

823
00:36:33,991 --> 00:36:35,626
as soon as possible?

824
00:36:37,161 --> 00:36:37,528
Yes.

825
00:36:41,365 --> 00:36:42,133
I'm going to surgery.

826
00:36:44,669 --> 00:36:46,103
When the artificial heart surgery happens,

827
00:36:46,103 --> 00:36:46,871
will you be the one operating?

828
00:36:47,772 --> 00:36:48,172
I don't know.

829
00:36:48,973 --> 00:36:49,607
It depends on the arrangement.

830
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:00,284
Brother.

831
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:02,753
The length of this cold war

832
00:37:02,787 --> 00:37:03,688
between you two—

833
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:05,189
is this

834
00:37:05,289 --> 00:37:06,023
a new record?

835
00:37:07,358 --> 00:37:08,759
You know he's in a bad state.

836
00:37:09,026 --> 00:37:10,628
His insomnia has worsened recently.

837
00:37:11,128 --> 00:37:12,663
Why don't one of you

838
00:37:13,631 --> 00:37:14,565
give the other a way out?

839
00:37:16,200 --> 00:37:17,368
I have nothing to say to him.

840
00:37:39,590 --> 00:37:39,924
Cut.

841
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:05,783
Can you close the chest?

842
00:38:11,856 --> 00:38:12,156
Yes.

843
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:13,591
Are you sure?

844
00:38:14,225 --> 00:38:14,692
I'm sure.

845
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:17,728
Then come over here.

846
00:38:18,295 --> 00:38:18,996
Liu Dong, supervise him.

847
00:38:31,175 --> 00:38:32,810
Director Lin wants me to close?

848
00:38:33,744 --> 00:38:34,345
He does.

849
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:37,448
Did I hear that right?

850
00:38:38,516 --> 00:38:39,550
Everyone heard it.

851
00:38:44,055 --> 00:38:45,623
The director is still behind you. Focus on the work.

852
00:38:54,398 --> 00:38:54,832
Sister Beibei.

853
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:56,067
Dr. Du.

854
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,401
I think Peng Mao

855
00:38:57,401 --> 00:38:58,069
is a little agitated today.

856
00:38:58,569 --> 00:38:59,470
His peak airway pressure rose

857
00:38:59,603 --> 00:39:00,571
from 25 to 32.

858
00:39:00,771 --> 00:39:01,639
His mean pressure is higher too.

859
00:39:02,039 --> 00:39:03,374
The oxygen concentration increased

860
00:39:03,474 --> 00:39:05,009
from 55 percent to 70 percent,

861
00:39:05,409 --> 00:39:06,444
but his oxygen saturation is only

862
00:39:06,444 --> 00:39:07,111
barely holding around 92.

863
00:39:07,311 --> 00:39:07,845
His heart rate is also fast.

864
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:09,680
Is the bedside chest X-ray back?

865
00:39:10,214 --> 00:39:10,915
I don't know. Let me check.

866
00:39:12,650 --> 00:39:13,117
It just came out.

867
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:13,918
Look.

868
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,121
There's so much fluid in the right pleural cavity.

869
00:39:27,465 --> 00:39:28,399
Breath sounds are weak too.

870
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:29,467
We need to perform thoracentesis quickly.

871
00:39:29,934 --> 00:39:30,601
Who's on duty tonight?

872
00:39:30,668 --> 00:39:31,202
Dr. Fang?

873
00:39:31,402 --> 00:39:32,570
Dr. Fang is at the medical consortium tonight.

874
00:39:32,803 --> 00:39:33,571
Dr. Yang is on duty.

875
00:39:34,038 --> 00:39:35,206
But he should be in the ward now.

876
00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:36,207
I'll call him.

877
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:37,074
Sister Beibei.

878
00:39:38,109 --> 00:39:38,976
This is urgent.

879
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:40,678
Prepare the thoracentesis kit.

880
00:40:24,054 --> 00:40:25,156
It feels like there's air.

881
00:40:33,631 --> 00:40:34,365
His oxygen saturation is dropping.

882
00:40:37,434 --> 00:40:38,102
Eighty.

883
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:39,069
No.

884
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:39,970
It's a pneumothorax.

885
00:40:46,744 --> 00:40:47,511
Breath sounds on the right

886
00:40:47,845 --> 00:40:48,445
have disappeared.

887
00:40:50,214 --> 00:40:51,682
Quick, increase the inspired oxygen.

888
00:40:51,882 --> 00:40:52,183
Okay.

889
00:40:54,919 --> 00:40:55,352
What happened?

890
00:40:55,786 --> 00:40:57,054
Call the physician on duty now.

891
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:57,354
Hurry.

892
00:40:57,488 --> 00:40:57,788
Okay.

893
00:41:07,198 --> 00:41:08,799
You know

894
00:41:08,833 --> 00:41:09,967
this patient's baseline condition is poor.

895
00:41:11,168 --> 00:41:12,236
You also know

896
00:41:12,269 --> 00:41:13,103
how difficult his family is.

897
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:15,306
They were already filing a complaint against us.

898
00:41:15,973 --> 00:41:16,607
And now, with what you did,

899
00:41:17,908 --> 00:41:18,409
you've made it worse.

900
00:41:19,076 --> 00:41:19,910
You've dragged everyone down with you.

901
00:41:21,712 --> 00:41:22,413
Explain yourself.

902
00:41:25,015 --> 00:41:26,450
At the time, the chest X-ray

903
00:41:26,450 --> 00:41:28,118
showed an obvious pleural effusion.

904
00:41:28,485 --> 00:41:30,120
The diagnosis was clear and it was urgent.

905
00:41:30,454 --> 00:41:32,156
I thought I'd first try

906
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,390
a small needle.

907
00:41:33,724 --> 00:41:35,192
What about ultrasound? Why didn't you use it?

908
00:41:35,726 --> 00:41:36,694
It was urgent,

909
00:41:36,794 --> 00:41:37,928
so I punctured directly.

910
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:40,130
And you punctured his lung.

911
00:41:41,198 --> 00:41:43,267
I'd successfully done it several times before.

912
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:44,568
More than once.

913
00:41:45,870 --> 00:41:47,204
This time, the needle may have gone

914
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:48,772
a little too deep.

915
00:41:49,306 --> 00:41:49,974
Where was your supervisor?

916
00:41:50,975 --> 00:41:51,475
I'm sorry.

917
00:41:52,042 --> 00:41:52,543
I bear responsibility.

918
00:41:52,610 --> 00:41:53,744
This has nothing to do with Dr. Fang.

919
00:41:54,044 --> 00:41:55,246
She wasn't on duty that night.

920
00:41:55,446 --> 00:41:56,547
Sister Beibei also asked me

921
00:41:56,614 --> 00:41:57,748
whether we should call the on-duty physician.

922
00:41:58,549 --> 00:41:59,049
Director,

923
00:41:59,483 --> 00:42:00,684
I overestimated my ability.

924
00:42:00,718 --> 00:42:01,719
This was entirely my fault.

925
00:42:02,553 --> 00:42:03,554
Let's first see

926
00:42:03,587 --> 00:42:04,388
how the patient's condition develops.

927
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:05,723
You all know

928
00:42:05,856 --> 00:42:07,324
how difficult Peng Mao's family is.

929
00:42:07,558 --> 00:42:08,626
If his condition

930
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:10,194
worsens because of this,

931
00:42:10,494 --> 00:42:11,629
none of us will get off lightly.

932
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,265
Both you and your supervisor are responsible.

933
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:19,069
A mistake is a mistake.

934
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:22,239
Whatever punishment is due, impose it.

935
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:24,608
I bear responsibility too.

936
00:42:25,442 --> 00:42:26,076
You weren't there.

937
00:42:26,243 --> 00:42:26,911
It happened in

938
00:42:26,944 --> 00:42:27,545
the general ICU.

939
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:28,145
It has nothing to do with you.

940
00:42:28,479 --> 00:42:29,547
He's only a specialty trainee.

941
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:31,148
What responsibility can he bear?

942
00:42:31,815 --> 00:42:32,750
He has always trained under me.

943
00:42:32,783 --> 00:42:33,784
I'm his supervisor.

944
00:42:34,451 --> 00:42:35,486
And I'm Peng Mao's primary surgeon.

945
00:42:36,153 --> 00:42:37,454
Any problem during the perioperative period

946
00:42:37,454 --> 00:42:38,188
should be my responsibility.

947
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:39,089
The incident happened

948
00:42:39,123 --> 00:42:40,190
in the general ICU.

949
00:42:40,357 --> 00:42:41,292
I'll communicate with the family

950
00:42:41,692 --> 00:42:42,726
and try to resolve it properly.

951
00:42:44,094 --> 00:42:44,728
That's all for now.

952
00:42:44,895 --> 00:42:45,963
We'll announce later

953
00:42:46,163 --> 00:42:47,398
the corresponding disciplinary measures.

954
00:42:48,599 --> 00:42:49,199
Begin handover.
